{# ── Country-visibility guard ──
   Reads the merchant-controlled `visibility_countries` (CSV) and
   `visibility_mode` ('show_in' | 'hide_in') settings, resolves the
   visitor's country via the shared detect-country partial, and decides
   whether to render this section.

   Why a separate detect partial: Vitrin's Jinja sandbox does NOT
   expose session/request/store globals inside macro bodies, so the
   country_visible macro can't detect internally. The include below
   runs in the parent context and CAN access them — its rendered
   output is captured into _detected_country, which is then passed
   to country_visible. Empty country list = always visible.
   See `country_visible` macro + `_detect-country.jinja` partial. #}
{% from 'components/_macros.jinja' import country_visible %}
{% set _detected_country %}{% include 'components/_detect-country.jinja' %}{% endset %}
{% set _detected_country = _detected_country | trim %}
{% set _section_visibility = country_visible(settings.visibility_countries, settings.visibility_mode, _detected_country) | trim %}
{% if _section_visibility == 'yes' %}
{# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   Highlights — compact USP / trust-badge strip (1–4 items).
   Each item: icon + title + subtitle, laid out horizontally.

   Display styles (`container_style`):
     • unified — single rounded container with thin vertical dividers
                 between items (no per-item borders). The "pill" look.
     • cards   — each item is its own bordered card with a gap between.
     • bare    — no borders, just spacing.

   This section is a thin wrapper: it resolves the merchant's settings
   into the shared `hl` namespace and delegates to the
   `components/highlights-render.jinja` partial. The same partial powers
   the header-level highlights strip (components/header-highlights.jinja),
   so the two stay visually and behaviourally in lock-step.

   Auto-id: section-ids.js sees `section-highlights` and assigns
   id="highlights-N" for in-page anchors / analytics.
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}

{# `points` instead of `items` — `settings.items` collides with the
   built-in dict.items() method, returning a bound method (no len) when
   the merchant hasn't added any rows yet. #}
{% set hl = {
  'points':           settings.points,
  'container_style':  settings.container_style | default('unified', true),
  'item_radius':      settings.item_radius if settings.item_radius is not none else 12,
  'background':       settings.background | default('secondary', true),
  'show_on_mobile':   true,
  'show_on_desktop':  true,
  'is_lazy':          settings.order > 2
} %}

{% set instance_id = sectionId %}
{% include 'components/highlights-render.jinja' %}
{% endif %}{# /country-visibility guard #}
